The '''Bunuban languages''' (or '''Bunaban''') are a small [[language family|family]] of [[Australian Aboriginal languages]] spoken in northern Australia. The family consists of two languages, '''[[Bunuba language|Bunuba]]''' and '''[[Gooniyandi language|Gooniyandi]]''', which are related to each other to about the same degree that English is related to Dutch. Bunuba has about 100 speakers and Gooniyandi about 400. Both are [[endangered languages|endangered]].

