'''Digital Learning Assets''' (''DLA''s) are any form of [[Content (media and publishing)|content]] and/or media that have been formatted into a [[binary code|binary]] source which include the right to use it for the purpose of "facilitating learning". DLAs are most commonly found in [[E-learning|online learning]] such as academic [[coursework]] and [[corporate training]]. <ref> Larson-Daugherty, C., February 2009 an update to van Nierkerk, A.J. (2006)</ref>

