{{for|the language|Siriano language}}
'''Siriano''' (also called "Selea" or "Sürá") are a [[Tucanoan languages|Tucanoan]] people indigenous to [[Colombia]] and [[Brazil]]. Their total population is estimated at 750, with most living in Colombia. Their [[exogamy|exogamous]] culture means that, [[glossology|glossologically]], speakers are identified by the first language of their father.<ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=sri Ethnologue]</ref> The [[Siriano language]] is [[Tucanoan languages|Tucanoan]].

